Outlier Detection in Kaduna State Presidential Election Data Using Geospatial Analysis

Gloria Olaniyan

Data Analyst | Driving Business Performance with Data-Driven Insights | Mentor & Speaker Empowering the Next Generation of Analysts | Python, SQL, Tableau, Power BI, Excel | HNG Finalist
July 4, 2024

Definition: An outlier is a data point significantly different from other data points in a dataset. This difference can be much higher or lower than the other values.

Context: In the recently concluded election, the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) faced numerous legal challenges regarding the integrity and accuracy of the election results. Allegations of vote manipulation and irregularities have been widespread, prompting a thorough investigation into the matter.

Objective: The goal is to identify polling units in Kaduna State where voting results deviate significantly from neighbouring units, indicating potential influences or rigging. We aim to detect outliers that may indicate irregularities by analyzing the geospatial data and voting results.

Data Overview:

  • Scope: 23 Local Government Areas (LGAs), 244 wards, and 6,130 polling units
  • Parties Involved: APC, PDP, LP, NNPP
  • Vote Counts: APC: 296,220 votes
  • PDP: 422,217 votes
  • LP: 231,855 votes
  • NNPP: 70,074 votes



  • Top 3 LGAs with Highest Votes: Kaduna South: 98,010 votes
  • Zaria: 91,456 votes
  • Chikun: 83,379 votes

Methodology:

  1. Data Collection: Obtained latitude and longitude for each polling unit address using geocoding.
  2. Grouping: Grouped polling units within each ward.
  3. Geospatial Analysis: Calculated distances between polling units to identify significant deviations in voting patterns.

Identifying Outliers in Ward ABORO


The sum of APC:

  • The highest value is 321(UNG MALLAM MUSA)
  • The lowest value is 0 (GONGORO).

The sum of PDP:

  • The highest value is 207(UNG MALLAM MUSA)
  • The lowest value is 0 (GONGORO).

The sum of LP:

  • The highest value is 133 (UNG MALLAM MUSA).
  • The lowest value is 0, which occurs multiple times.

The sum of NNPP:

  • The highest value is 5 (ABORO II).
  • The lowest value is 0, which occurs multiple times.

Identifying Outliers in Ward AGUNU


The first two polling units in the table above exhibit significant outliers in the vote counts for the ward Agunu:

  1. SAKWAI HANYA shows a remarkably high number of votes for the APC (461 votes), PDP(57 votes), and NNPP(19 VOTES).
  2. GRAZING has notably the same number of votes as SAKWAI HANYA.


Identifying Outliers in Ward BITAL


Notable Outliers:

  • UNGIDI K/G MAI UNGUWA: Has a high value for APC (224).
  • KINUGY L.E.A PRY SCHOOL: Has the highest value for PDP (146).
  • KUSHEKA II L.E.A. PRY SCHOOL and FARIN DUTSE K/G MAIUNGUEWA: Have the same votes for the four parties.
